# Sanitize public repo content

SubConscious-Adapter is public. Do not commit live Hermes or host-specific secrets.

## Never commit

- Full `~/.hermes/config.yaml`
- API keys, tokens, session IDs, email addresses
- Production cron job UUIDs or operator-specific paths

## Safe to include

- `plugin.yaml`, `README.md`, `UPGRADE-HERMES-version.md`
- `examples/hermes-gateway.snippet.yaml` (subconscious platform excerpt only)

For engine config, inbox, and cron howtos, follow SubConscious-Engine `docs/CRON-AND-INBOX.md` and `.cursor/rules/sanitize-public-content.mdc` there.

Before commit: grep for `api_key`, `token`, `@`, `/home/`, `\bRev\b`, `\bKarla\b`, and real hostnames.
